# UI Styleguide Rules

## Canonical source

- The **single source of truth** for UI is `docs/ui/styleguide.md`.
- All assistants (Cursor, Claude) and contributors must follow that file for:
  - Colors and dark/light treatment
  - Layout and card patterns
  - Forms (inputs, labels, errors, buttons)
  - Feedback (inline errors, toasts)

## Auth and onboarding flows

- Use the **full-screen dark auth layout**:
  - Outer container: `dark min-h-screen bg-[#0a0a0a] text-white flex items-center justify-center p-4`
  - Back link: top-left, subtle, `text-zinc-500 hover:text-white`
  - Centered card: `w-full max-w-md px-4`
- Reuse the structure from:
  - Angular: `signin.page.ts`, `signup.page.ts`
  - React: `LoginPage.tsx`, `RegisterPage.tsx`
- Only change **content** (copy, fields) unless the styleguide itself is being updated.

## General layout & components

- Prefer semantic tokens wired via `styles.scss`:
  - `bg-background text-foreground` for main surfaces
  - `bg-card text-card-foreground border-border` for cards
  - `text-muted-foreground` or `text-zinc-500` for secondary text
- Keep a consistent vertical rhythm using `space-y-4` / `space-y-6`.
- Use existing primitives:
  - Angular: spartan-ng helm components (`@spartan-ng/helm/*`, `hlmBtn`)
  - React: `AI Marketing Platform/src/app/components/ui/*`

## Forms and validation

- Labels: `text-xs text-zinc-400 mb-2 block` above controls.
- Auth inputs: `h-11 w-full rounded-lg border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900 px-3 text-sm text-white placeholder:text-zinc-600`.
- Errors:
  - Field errors: `mt-1 text-xs text-red-400` (or `text-destructive` on light).
  - Form-level error: short message above primary button.
- Buttons on dark auth:
  - Primary: `w-full h-11 bg-white text-black hover:bg-zinc-200 text-sm`, disabled while submitting.

## When generating new UI

- **Always** consult `docs/ui/styleguide.md` before adding or refactoring UI.
- Do not introduce new ad-hoc colors, radii, or layout patterns without updating the styleguide.
- For small variants, start from existing auth/cards/forms and tweak minimally.

